The metrics include total number of jobs executed in a day, total/average/max time across all datameer jobs submitted in a day.  High spikes might indicate unusual Datameer job activity.

widgets.textContent: The widgets in this page pertain to performance of the Job Scheduler.  For example, how long does it take to prepare jobs, marking previous execution results as obsolete, and average busy ratio.

widgets.name: Text 3
widgets.textContent: The widgets of this page reveal information on how often scheduled jobs run.  Each cron expression is scored and the higher the value, the more frequent the job runs.  This page should help administrators understand what are the jobs that run most frequently and take appropriate action.

widgets.name: Text 3
widgets.textContent: This page can help Datameer Administrators understand what are the most popular schedules.  With this information, Datameer administrators can make sure that unnecessary jobs are not scheduled.

widgets.name: Text 3
widgets.textContent: This page reveals the busiest day of the week, time of the day, and a combination of both.  Datameer Administrators should be able to leverage this graph and identify what timeframes look adequate to perform maintenance or execute ad hoc jobs.
